Montane. The nomenclature of forest, woodland and thicket follows definitions by Beard and Fanshawe. The series of subformations within each formation are broadly correlated with gradients of temperature (altitude or latitude), soil properties (moisture, drainage, fertility) and exposure. The sharp ecological segregation of Rain forests from the autochthonous sclerophyll flora is closely related to soil nutrient status (influenced by fire) as well as to temperature and moisture conditions and historical f{\textbackslash}ldots},
